text:
A general (aerial) view north from Bleecker Street, between Thompson and Sullivan Streets, showing at the left, Sixth Ave., north from and including West 3rd., Street. Washington Square Park and the beginning of Fifth Ave., are in the centre, and in the background is Bryant Park.

About 1925.

Fairchild Aerial Service.
title: General view - Bleecker Street - North.

text:
203 to 231 Thompson Street, west side, between Bleecker and West 3rd (formerly Amity) Streets, and towards West 3rd. No. 207-213, shown "for rent" in this view, is the former Z. T. Piercy stables. May 23, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.

Bleecker Street, east from Thompson Street. Shown on West Broadway, is the Bleecker Street Station of the Sixth Ave. Elevated Line.

June 23, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

Bleecker Street, southeast corner and Thompson Street, from the northwest corner looking southeast. Village Hotel, on corner

P. L. Sperr

April 30, 1940
